<h1>My spouse (or co-worker) loves to antagonize me, especially at the most inopportune times!</h1>
<p>First, count to 10 before you say or do something you will regret. If possible, step away from the situation so that you can take a time-out to take a few deep breaths or stretch. You can say, “I can see that you are upset and I just need a moment before responding, so I’m going to step out of the room for a moment.”</p>

